The English Garden - February 2014  UK

116 Pages | HQ PDF | English | 45 MB 


Join us and every issue you will enjoy beautiful gardens - as we explore some of the loveliest gardens in the country, and talk to the gardeners who made them - from traditional herbaceous borders, through the clipped splendour of topiary, and onto town gardens or even the exuberant colours of wildflower meadows.
